            <title>[CASSANDRA-3922] streaming from all (not one) neighbors during rebuild/bootstrap</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-3922</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The last round of changes that happened in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-3483&quot; title=&quot;Support bringing up a new datacenter to existing cluster without repair&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-3483&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-3483&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; before it went in actually changed behavior - we now stream from &lt;b&gt;ALL&lt;/b&gt; neighbors that have a range, rather than just one. This leads to data size explosion.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Attaching patch to revert to intended behavior.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
